<br>
Ok I will bite, how exactly is this cheating?<br>
<br>
It's using an automated method to mass produce something with minimal effort on the part of the owner. Much like Henry Ford did back in the beginning of the 20th century. You think the other 2 car manufacturers came to him and said, &quot;Well at least we aren't cheating!&quot;<br>
<br>
If, by deifinition of cheating, you define it as using a 3rd party program. Then yes. Does it allow them to get an unfair advantage? Not really, it still has to go through all the same motions that you do manually. Sure it can probably last longer, but how much longer? Bags can only carry so much, much like yours. <br>
<br>
So once again, how is this cheating, other than the lame 3rd party program argument, because that one doesn't float with them allowing ctrl-alt-del and windowed mode now. <p><a href=http://www.hneguild.com/profile.asp?name=Garbhad><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~cblack87/Garbsig.jpeg"></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=garbhad>Garbhad</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_2.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/13/03 9:27:16 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seani>Seani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 533<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/13/03 11:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3159.topic&index=79>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wow</span><hr size=1> The answer, Garb, is based on perceived, implied, or stated intent of the game designers.  Macroquest allows someone to advance in skill much faster than was intended by the designers of the game.  The tradeskill systems are by design supposed to take a long time.  Whenever shortcuts are introduced or discovered, they are promptly removed to restore the tedium and expense of skilling up.  <br>
<br>
Working around the intent of the game designers (especially when the end result is that you become more powerful than others) is cheating in the eyes of most players.  Disagree if you like, but that's what most players believe.<br>
<br>
